# Pluto - AI-Powered Code Security Analyzer

Pluto is a powerful CLI tool that uses AI to detect security vulnerabilities in your code.

## Features

- 🤖 Multiple AI providers: Claude, OpenAI, Ollama (local)
- 📁 Analyze files, directories, or GitHub repositories
- 📊 Multiple report formats: Terminal, PDF, JSON, Markdown
- 🔒 Privacy-first with local Ollama support
- 🎯 Severity filtering (CRITICAL, HIGH, MEDIUM, LOW)

## Installation

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/pluto.git
cd pluto

# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Install Pluto
pip install -e .
```

## Setup

### For Claude (Recommended)
```bash
export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY='your-api-key-here'
```

### For OpenAI
```bash
export OPENAI_API_KEY='your-api-key-here'
```

### For Ollama (Local, Free)
```bash
# Install Ollama from https://ollama.ai
ollama pull codellama
ollama serve
```

## Usage

### Analyze a single file
```bash
pluto scan -code app.py
```

### Analyze entire directory
```bash
pluto scan -dir ./src --report pdf --output security_report
```

### Analyze GitHub repository
```bash
pluto scan -git https://github.com/user/repo --provider claude
```

### Use local AI (Ollama)
```bash
pluto scan -code app.py --provider ollama --model codellama
```

### Filter by severity
```bash
pluto scan -dir ./src --min-severity HIGH
```

### Generate different report formats
```bash
pluto scan -code app.py --report json --output results
pluto scan -code app.py --report pdf --output security_audit
pluto scan -code app.py --report markdown --output findings
```

## Supported Languages

Python, JavaScript, TypeScript, Java, C/C++, Go, Rust, PHP, Ruby, Swift, Kotlin

## Security Checks

- SQL Injection
- XSS (Cross-Site Scripting)
- Authentication/Authorization flaws
- Hardcoded secrets
- Insecure cryptography
- Path traversal
- Command injection
- CSRF vulnerabilities
- And more...

